ANY EXISTING RELEVANT MEDICAL ISSUES
CURRENT MEDICATIONS: sertraline, magnesium supplement

So this is following on from my previous post on this sub about testicular pain.
I went to see the doctor about it and at first he thought it might be a hernia, then decided it might be orchitis (he seemed pretty unsure either way).
He prescribed me doxycycline for one week.
I read the long (LONG) list of side effects and... yeah, now I'm scared.

I'm not sure, but I feel like the pain may be getting better, or at least lessening. It's not constant throughout the day.

If the doctor isn't sure what's wrong, should I actually take them, especially with all the unpleasant or just plain dangerous side effects?
